Title: An Act to Require Utilities to Monitor Meters for Natural Gas
Official Title: An Act to Require Utilities to Monitor Meters for Natural Gas
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1473
H.P. 965 House of Representatives, April 3, 2025
Leaks
Reference to the Committee on Energy, Utilities and Technology suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative WARREN of Scarborough.
Cosponsored by Representatives: FAIRCLOTH of Bangor, GEIGER of Rockland, WEBB of
Durham.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §4713 is enacted to read:
3 §4713. Monitoring of natural gas meters
4 1. Utilities to monitor meters for natural gas leaks. A gas utility shall monitor every
5 natural gas meter under its jurisdiction for leaks and report annually to the commission on
6 the number of leaks identified under this section and any action taken by the utility to
7 address the leaks. The commission shall contract a qualified impartial 3rd party to
8 periodically assess utility compliance with this section in a frequency determined by the
9 commission.
10 2. Rules. The commission shall adopt rules to carry out the purposes of this section.
11 Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical rules under Title 5, chapter
12 375, subchapter 2-A.
13 SUMMARY
1144 This bill directs gas utilities to monitor the utilities' natural gas meters for leaks and
1155 report annually to the Public Utilities Commission on the number of leaks identified and
1166 any action taken to address the leaks. The bill requires the Public Utilities Commission to
1177 contract a qualified impartial 3rd party to periodically assess utility compliance with the
1188 monitoring and reporting requirements. The bill directs the Public Utilities Commission to
1199 adopt routine technical rules to carry out the purposes of the provisions of the bill.
